s":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Prep your fresh artichokes by trimming the stem, removing the top 1/3 of it using a serrated knife.","name":"Prep your fresh artichokes by trimming the stem, removing the top 1/3 of it using a serrated knife.","url":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/#wprm-recipe-12365-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Using kitchen sheers, trim the tips of leaves.","name":"Using kitchen sheers, trim the tips of leaves.","url":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/#wprm-recipe-12365-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Rinse your artichokes under water, spreading out the leaves to let water inside the artichoke&#039;s layers.","name":"Rinse your artichokes under water, spreading out the leaves to let water inside the artichoke&#039;s layers.","url":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/#wprm-recipe-12365-step-0-2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Take lemon wedges and rub over the cut sections of the the artichoke. This step helps to minimize browning/oxidization","name":"Take lemon wedges and rub over the cut sections of the the artichoke. This step helps to minimize browning/oxidization","url":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/#wprm-recipe-12365-step-0-3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place garlic, lemon wedges and fresh herbs (if using) in your Instant Pot.","name":"Place garlic, lemon wedges and fresh herbs (if using) in your Instant Pot.","url":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/#wprm-recipe-12365-step-0-4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place the Instant Pot trivet on top and gentle pour the water into the Instant Pot.","name":"Place the Instant Pot trivet on top and gentle pour the water into the Instant Pot.","url":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/#wprm-recipe-12365-step-0-5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Arrange your artichokes upside down in your Instant Pot on top of the trivet in a single layer.","name":"Arrange your artichokes upside down in your Instant Pot on top of the trivet in a single layer.","url":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/#wprm-recipe-12365-step-0-6"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place the lid on your Instant Pot and lock it into place. Be sure the release valve on the top is closed.","name":"Place the lid on your Instant Pot and lock it into place. Be sure the release valve on the top is closed.","url":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/#wprm-recipe-12365-step-0-7"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Using the manual mode, cook the artichokes on HIGH pressure for 15 minutes. It will take your Instant Pot about 10 minutes to get up to pressure.","name":"Using the manual mode, cook the artichokes on HIGH pressure for 15 minutes. It will take your Instant Pot about 10 minutes to get up to pressure.","url":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/#wprm-recipe-12365-step-0-8"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Once cook time is up, quick release the pressure.","name":"Once cook time is up, quick release the pressure.","url":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/#wprm-recipe-12365-step-0-9"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Once the pressure is completely released, carefully unlock and remove the lid of your Instant Pot.","name":"Once the pressure is completely released, carefully unlock and remove the lid of your Instant Pot.","url":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/#wprm-recipe-12365-step-0-10"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Carefully remove artichokes with tongs or a large spoon. Slice in half and enjoy warm with your favorite dipping sauce or as is!","name":"Carefully remove artichokes with tongs or a large spoon. Slice in half and enjoy warm with your favorite dipping sauce or as is!","url":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/#wprm-recipe-12365-step-0-11"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.62","ratingCount":"13"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"4"},"reviewBody":"I grow artichokes in my garden. The ones you have pictured are perfect and really don’t need all the trimming!  Keep it easy. Unless you r artichokes have the super prickly tips, save yourself time and skip it! Wash and cook! Also, no need to cut in half for eating! Just pluck off the leaves. ","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Gina"},"datePublished":"2024-06-04"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"1"},"reviewBody":"Well I just ruined four beautiful artichokes. They are absolute MUSH. Total baby food. I’ve never overcooked artichokes this badly. I should have looked at literally every other site that says 15 min and then release pressure immediately. Letting them sit there for another 15 min of natural release was a mess. I’m so sad. They were big beautiful chokes. ","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Summer Fracé"},"datePublished":"2024-03-22"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Thanks so much for this. We live in Albuquerque and the mile-high altitude can be problematic but the Instant Pot pressure can help enormously. The artichokes were perfect following your instuctions! Thanks again.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Marj"},"datePublished":"2024-03-07"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I didn't know I could cook an artichoke in the instant pot. I just never thought about it until today. I'm now happy to cook it. They used to be so tedious and sometimes not so tasty. This is going into my food rotation. Thank you!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"KATHERINE MacArthur-Krall"},"datePublished":"2024-01-20"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I think Nancy and I have the same Instant Pot.  We have a button that says “Pressure Cooker” and then a buttons to set high or low pressure.  So you press “Pressure Cooker,” then set it to high pressure, and then set the cooking time.\r\n\r\nJust FYI in case someone else has the same question.  Pressure Cooker button is our manual button.  It’s the 3 quart Instant Pot.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Shannon Duane"},"datePublished":"2022-04-24"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Taesha- Thank you for the assistance on cooking artihokes in the one-pot....I will recommend, however, that you change the picture to show the artichokes actually upside down....for those of us who have cooked them before, the picture contradicts your instructions......just a thought..","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Michele"},"datePublished":"2022-02-23"}],"recipeCategory":["Side Dish"],"recipeCuisine":["American"],"keywords":"easy artichoke recipe, how to cook fresh artichoke","nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","servingSize":"1 artichoke","calories":"205 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"47 g","proteinContent":"14 g","fatContent":"1 g","saturatedFatContent":"1 g","sodiumContent":"381 mg","fiberContent":"22 g","sugarContent":"5 g"},"@id":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https://thenaturalnurturer.com/instant-pot-artichokes/"}]}</script>

