<p><img class="wprm-comment-rating" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODdhAQABAPAAAP///wAAACwAAAAAAQABAEACAkQBADs=" data-lazy-src="https://thenaturalnurturer.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-recipe-maker/assets/icons/rating/stars-1.svg" alt="1 star" width="80" height="16" /><br/>
Well I just ruined four beautiful artichokes. They are absolute MUSH. Total baby food. I’ve never overcooked artichokes this badly. I should have looked at literally every other site that says 15 min and then release pressure immediately. Letting them sit there for another 15 min of natural release was a mess. I’m so sad. They were big beautiful chokes. </p>
