<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-33176" data-commentid="33176" data-postid="12255" data-belowelement="comment-33176" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Taesha Butler" aria-label="Reply to Taesha Butler">Reply</a> </div>
<p>Hi Summer. Sorry to hear your artichokes were too soft for you. I’ve tested this recipe many times and with many different times. I found that quick releasing the pressure after 15 minutes left me with a tough artichoke more often than not. Which is why I went with the natural release method. Artichokes can also vary in density and size. Perhaps your artichokes were smaller than mine. Or less dense. Or I just prefer them softer. </p>
<p>Regardless, I appreciate the honest feedback and think it’s can be helpful to others. I’ll definitely update the recipe mention adjusting cooking time for personal preference.</p>
